import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['lat'], bins=20, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['lat'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['lat'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['lat'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['lat'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Latitude')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['key'] = pd.to_numeric(data['key'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['key'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.hist(data['key'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(x=data['key'].min(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Min: {data['key'].min():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(x=data['key'].max(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {data['key'].max():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    ax.set_xlabel('Key')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title("What is the range of values for the 'key' field in the dataset?")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['key'], data['lat'], color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Key')
    plt.ylabel('Lat')
    plt.title("Is there a correlation between 'key' and 'lat' fields in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.boxplot(data['lat'])
    plt.axhline(y=data['lat'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='-', label=f"Mean: {data['lat'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks([1], ['lat'])
    plt.xlabel('Field')
    plt.ylabel('Value')
    plt.title("What is the average value of 'lat' field in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
